olar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">6.</div><div id="r6" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Levy AD, Manning MA, Al-Refaie WB, Miettinen MM. Soft-tissue sarcomas of the abdomen and pelvis: radiologic-pathologic features. I. Common sarcomas. <em>RadioGraphics</em> 2017;37(2):462–483.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1148/rg.2017160157">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/28287938/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Soft-tissue+sarcomas+of+the+abdomen+and+pelvis%3A+radiologic-pathologic+features.+I.+Common+sarcomas&amp;author=AD+Levy&amp;author=MA+Manning&amp;author=WB+Al-Refaie&amp;author=MM+Miettinen&amp;publication_year=2017&amp;journal=RadioGraphics&amp;pages=462-483&amp;doi=10.1148%2Frg.2017160157&amp;pmid=28287938">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">7.</div><div id="r7" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Levy AD, Manning MA, Miettinen MM. Soft-tissue sarcomas of the abdomen and pelvis: radiologic-pathologic features. II. Uncommon sarcomas. <em>RadioGraphics</em> 2017;37(3):797–812.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1148/rg.2017160201">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/28493803/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Soft-tissue+sarcomas+of+the+abdomen+and+pelvis%3A+radiologic-pathologic+features.+II.+Uncommon+sarcomas&amp;author=AD+Levy&amp;author=MA+Manning&amp;author=MM+Miettinen&amp;publication_year=2017&amp;journal=RadioGraphics&amp;pages=797-812&amp;doi=10.1148%2Frg.2017160201&amp;pmid=28493803">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">8.</div><div id="r8" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Akbulut S, Yavuz R, Otan E, Hatipoglu S. Pancreatic extragastrointestinal stromal tumor: a case report and comprehensive literature review. <em>World J Gastrointest Surg</em> 2014;6(9):175–182.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.4240/wjgs.v6.i9.175">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/25276287/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Pancreatic+extragastrointestinal+stromal+tumor%3A+a+case+report+and+comprehensive+literature+review&amp;author=S+Akbulut&amp;author=R+Yavuz&amp;author=E+Otan&amp;author=S+Hatipoglu&amp;publication_year=2014&amp;journal=World+J+Gastrointest+Surg&amp;pages=175-182&amp;doi=10.4240%2Fwjgs.v6.i9.175&amp;pmid=25276287">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">9.</div><div id="r9" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Miettinen M, Felisiak-Golabek A, Wang Z, Inaguma S, Lasota J. GIST manifesting as a retroperitoneal tumor: clinicopathologic, immunohistochemical, and molecular genetic study of 112 cases. <em>Am J Surg Pathol</em> 2017;41(5):577–585.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1097/PAS.0000000000000807">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/28288036/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=GIST+manifesting+as+a+retroperitoneal+tumor%3A+clinicopathologic%2C+immunohistochemical%2C+and+molecular+genetic+study+of+112+cases&amp;author=M+Miettinen&amp;author=A+Felisiak-Golabek&amp;aut